The enhanced IPEC properties of the two PbS/Ro-GO/PANI/ITO glass and Au/PbS/Ro-GO/PANI nano/microcomposite membrane electrodes are further confirmed by measuring the incident photon-to-current conversion efficiency (IPCE) under monochromatic illumination conditions as shown in Fig. 8(A,B), respectively. Such analytical measurements can also give a meaningful insight into the contribution of PbS/Ro-GO/PANI nano/microcomposite in the conversion of the incident photons into charge carriers. The IPCE is determined at an applied potential of 1 V from Eq. (3)59:3IPCE(%)=1240.Jphλ.ρ.100\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
